diskarzhañ
==========

A stupide include cleaner for standard headers.

Instead of trying to be smart, diskarzhañ maintains a mapping of symbols provided
by a header, greps for those symbols in files, and remove headers if no symbols
are found.

If your code was relying on transitive include, diskarzhañ does not try to help
you, it removes the non-minimal include and then you'll need to add the missing
minimal ones.

Once you reach a stable situation, you can use diskarzhañ in CI to prevent
regression.

Because diskarzhañ does not compile ypur code, it is configuration independant and
runs very fast. It sometimes misses some unused headers but should not remove
used ones. If so... fill a bug!

diskarzhañ has been initially developped as an anonymous linter for the Firefox
codebase. It is shared here as a standalone tool for ease of distribution.

/trugarez ha ken ar cʼhentañ gwel/
